<br>
These dragons were designed when 50 was the ultimate, remember, and I bet that the first folks who took down Vox and Nagafen didn't wait until they were 49 (or 47) to try it.<br>
<br>
It's about fun, mostly, for me, not the l3wt or the &quot;success&quot; of the raid (if I and others with me had fun and learned something, then it was a success in my eyes whether the dragon dies or not -- granted it's a BETTER success if they DO die  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). <p>Tryllium Calaquendi -- Cleric of Tunare, 45th Circle<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalazar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valazar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/11/01 3:35:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Nagafen/Vox</span><hr size=1> Speaking as a non-guild player who has been on 10 Vox raids (9 successful), I find very little to object to with the current system.  I've never been refused membership on any raid I wanted to join, and I've met alot of great people from many guilds in the process.<br>
<br>
I have never walked off with any loot, but not because I didn't try.  The eyepatch would be great, but honestly I WANT the WHITE SCALE.  That White Dragonscale Cloak quest has been a goal of mine for a loooong time.  I figured from the begining that I'd have to pay my dues and contribute on many raids before I got the payoff. I don't mind.  I contribute, and some day I'll get it, that is if I don't die of old age (lvl 53) first. I started at 46 and am now about to turn 52.  I hope my lucky number turns up soon.<br>
<br>
No, most of the guilds probably cannot field the complete force of 46-52 lvl players needed to take out Vox (or Naggy), but so what?  As a social event, it gives the guild a chance to interact with other players who may be interested in joining.  Let the guild claim duplicate drops, but also let EVERYONE who Can-And-Will-Use an item roll for it.  Verant screwed us once more by putting scarce standard quest items into an EPIC quest.  An EPIC item should be harder to get than a common quest, and ...<br>
<br>
*********************************<br>
  just because it's an EPIC item doesn't give the class questing for it the right to stomp all over everyone else who CaWu that item.  Take a number and get in line!!!!<br>
*********************************<br>
<br>
Don't change the system, but do modify the standards for looting to be fair to all players.<br>
<br>
Looking forward to a few more good raids (and just 1 White Scale)...<br>
<br>
Valazar Valorovich<br>
51st Channeler<br>
