<br>
What I am trying to say is, that if you take the scale and turn it in for the cloak, that is one less scale that can be used for an epic.  Why not just trade the scale for a heiro cloak or another white scale cloak and give someone the opportunity to finish an epic.  Which benefits anyone who groups with that bard?<br>
<br>
To me, to use the scale for the cloak and lessen the chances for an epic on our server seems a bit selfish.  But that is just my opinion. <br>
<br>
I have been on 7 Vox raids now and have only seen the scale drop once.  So a caster could have 1 cloak which is not even the best cloak they can wear anymore, or a bard has a chance at his or her epic, which can not be replaced in any way.<br>
<br>
What seems more fair to you?<br>
<br>
It is the same with the red scale.  The red scale BP is a nice item, but there is better out there now I believe.  But both bards and warriors need that scale for their epic.  I think it is sad to use that item for anything that isn't an epic.<br>
<br>
It is sad that Verant has made the quests this way.  But isn't a one of a kind item better than an item that will be upgraded later? <p><center>
