<br>
I cannot think of a cloak better than a WDSC, but I do agree that the epic need of the scale should outweigh the need of a WDSC for a caster.  I would like to see a compromise made for this, perhaps as allowing casters on the scale roll with the definitive condition that the scale NOT be turned into a WDSC, but traded for one (I know Sedusar has one to trade).  I would not even discount the trade for a Heirophant's Cloak or Tobrin's Mystical Eyepatch, as these have entered the economy on occasion and are on-par with the WDSC for a caster.   Then the bards on the raid should roll for the rights to the scale and be given a certain amount of time to come up with a an acceptable substitute before it passes to another bard from the raid, and eventually bards outside the raid.<br>
<br>
Mainly, I think the priority is to not let a white scale leave the world without it being part of a bard epic.<br>
<br>
I don't think the red scale should be able to turned for a BP.  There are many alternatives of varying difficulties, but I would hate to deny someone a chance at their epic for what has become a mediocre breastplate. <p><p><font face="Arial">Hawkline Monster<br>
